The paper deals with named entity recognition and linking, which are important tasks in information retrieval and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.DB (Databases) are likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes graph-based methods for named entity identification, which involve machine learning and data mining techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper compares its approach with recent deep learning methods, indicating a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
